Interface FileTransferProgressData

public interface FileTransferProgressData

Reports file transfer progress monitoring data.

Method Detail

getBytesTransferred

long getBytesTransferred()
Returns the number of bytes transferred so far.

This number not only counts the number of bytes transferred by the current file transfer session, but also adds in the bytes transferred by previous interrupted transfers, if any. Subtract getResumedAtSize() to get the bytes transferred by the current session.

Returns:
The number of bytes transferred so far.

getFileSize

long getFileSize()
Returns the size of the file being transferred.

This number will remain constant for the entire file transfer session.

Returns:
The size of the file in bytes.

getResumedAtSize

long getResumedAtSize()
Returns the point in the file where the transfer was resumed.

This number will remain constant for the entire file transfer session.

Returns:
The number of bytes transferred previously.
